{{wikipedia}}
==English==
===Pronunciation===
*bû(r)ch, /bɜː(r)tʃ/, /b3:(r)tS/
*:[[Rhymes:English:-ɜː(r)tʃ|Rhymes: -ɜː(r)tʃ]]
===Etymology===
Old English ''birce'', ''bierce'', ''[[beorc]]''
===Noun===
{{en-noun|es}}
# any of various [[tree]]s of the genus ''[[Betula]]'', native to countries in the [[northern hemisphere]].
# a hard wood taken from the birch tree, typically used to make furniture.
# a stick, rod or bundle of twigs made from birch wood, used for punishment.

